This package provides an R (S4) interface to "shotgun", the (large-scale)
parallel coordinate decent solver for lasso and sparse logistic regression
written in C++

Shotgun is developed by Aapo Kyrola, Joseph Bradley Danny Bickson, and
Carlos Guestrin in the SELECT lab at CMU.

For more information about shotgun, please see: 

  SELECT lab: http://select.cs.cmu.edu/people/index.html
  Shotgun homepage: http://select.cs.cmu.edu/code/
  ICML 2011 paper: http://arxiv.org/abs/1105.5379

See the buckshot wiki for a quick overview:

  https://github.com/lianos/buckshot/wiki

The buckshot library is neither endorsed or supported by the authors of the
shotgun library.

buckshot is released under the Apache 2 License, which is the same license the
shotgun library is released under. It should go without saying, but buckshot is
provided AS IS and with NO WARRANTY.

